Reebok Zig Kinetica II The Jetstones Rosie the Robot
results.story: The Reebok Zig Kinetica 2 ‘Rosie’ is taken from the ‘Flintstones Meet Jetsons’ collection, inspired by a 1987 made-for-TV movie that united two classic Hanna-Barbera series in a cartoon crossover event. This pair mimics the look of the Jetsons’ robot maid Rosie, featuring varying shades of blue throughout a textile upper overlaid with translucent no-dew skins. A sculpted white tongue represents Rosie’s signature cap, while the robot’s model number is listed on the black webbing heel pull. Lightweight cushioning is provided by a Floatride Fuel midsole, wrapped in a solid black Zig Energy Shell for added responsiveness.

results.name: Reebok Club C Legacy The Jetsons Jane Jetson
results.story: The Reebok Club C Legacy ‘Jane Jetson’ is taken from the ‘Flintstones Meet Jetsons’ collection, inspired by a 1987 made-for-TV movie that brought together two classic Hanna-Barbera series. This pair utilizes a Brilliant Pink leather upper reminiscent of Judy Jetson’s two-piece dress. Metallic silver detailing on the eyestay, coupled with translucent rubber tooling, symbolizes The Jetsons’ futuristic milieu. Underfoot, the outsole features custom graphics that reference Jane’s beauty regimen and the robots who help her prepare.

results.name: Reebok Zig Kinetica II The Flintstones The Great Gazoo
results.story: Launching as part of the ‘Flintstones Meet Jetsons’ collection, the Reebok Zig Kinetica 2 ‘The Great Gazoo’ draws inspiration from a 1987 made-for-TV movie that merged two classic Hanna-Barbera series. Paying tribute to Fred and Barney’s extraterrestrial foil, the lifestyle runner sports a Flora Green mesh upper with protruding antennae-like eyelets. The Great Gazoo’s signature greeting — ‘Hello Dum Dum’ — is inscribed across a pair of black webbing heel pulls. A glow-in-the-dark TPU cage features the same distinctive zigzag shape that frames the Floatride Fuel midsole.

results.name: Reebok Shaqnosis The Big Aristotle
results.story: The Reebok Shaqnosis ‘Big Aristotle’ references Shaquille O’Neal’s self-imposed nickname with a unique design inspired by ancient Greek architecture. A subtle marbled finish distinguishes the off-white leather upper, featuring the shoe’s signature arcing overlays in tonal suede. An unexpected pop of color arrives via a purple suede heel tab marked with Shaq’s Dunkman logo. The mid-top rests on a lightweight EVA midsole with visible Hexalite cushioning in the heel.

Reebok Zig Kinetica II Edge Brown Green
results.story: The Reebok Zig Kinetica 2 ‘Edge’ brings subdued earth tones to a trail-inspired silhouette built for rugged terrain. Toggle lacing secures the patterned grey textile upper, reinforced with forefoot and heel overlays in tan and green. Vibrant pops of color arrive via pink contrast stitching and a pair of yellow webbing pull tabs. The sneaker is mounted on a lightly speckled Floatride Fuel midsole, supported by an anti-slip Vibram Ecostep outsole with aggressive outdoor lugs.

results.name: Reebok Club C Legacy Keith Haring Three-Eyed Smiling Face
results.story: Launching as part of a five-piece footwear collection celebrating the iconic street artist, the Keith Haring x Reebok Club C Legacy ‘Three-Eyed Smiling Face’ dresses the tennis-inspired silhouette in smooth red leather. On the lateral quarter panel, Reebok branding accompanies a graphic depicting Haring’s three-eyed smiling face. A second Reebok wordmark is stamped on the heel tab, while the artist’s signature is scrawled on the woven tongue tag and custom sockliner. The vivid scarlet hue up top is countered by a rubber cupsole in a neutral grey finish.

results.name: Reebok GL 6000 Keith Haring Pure Primary Colors
results.story: Taken from a five-piece collection inspired by the ‘80s street art icon, the Keith Haring x Reebok GL 6000 ‘Dog and Human Heel Print’ updates the retro runner with a verdant color palette. The upper is crafted from bright green nylon with contrasting white side stripes and tonal overlays in leather and suede. Keith Haring’s canine and human figures are embroidered on the back heel, while the artist’s signature is scrawled on the woven tongue tag and sockliner. Color-popped accents in yellow and orange enliven the white EVA midsole, supported underfoot by a solid black rubber outsole.

results.name: Reebok Classic Leather Legacy AZ Keith Haring Dancing Figures
results.story: The Keith Haring x Reebok Classic Leather Legacy AZ ‘Dancing Figures Heel Print’ represents one of five models that make up a limited footwear collection centered around the street art icon. The upper is constructed from white textile with blue leather side stripes and reinforced overlays in grey suede and white leather. Unique branding elements include the artist’s signature on the tongue tag and a trio of his dancing figures stamped on the suede heel tab. Lightweight cushioning arrives via a die-cut EVA midsole, supported underfoot by a cored-out black rubber outsole.

results.name: Reebok Pump Omni Zone II Juun.J White
results.story: The Juun J x Reebok Pump Omni Zone 2 ‘White Cold Grey’ is taken from a three-piece pack developed in partnership with the Korean fashion designer. Juun’s elevated take on the retro ‘90s hoops shoe features a grey premium leather upper with perforated detailing on the tox box and quarter panel. Reebok’s Pump technology combines with leather laces to a deliver a secure fit. ‘Juun J’ is embossed on an added TPU heel piece in a glossy white finish, complementing the wavy midfoot cage brought over from the original design. The sneaker rides on an EVA midsole with Hexalite cushioning, visible through a cut-out window in the rubber outsole.

results.name: Reebok Pump Omni Zone II Juun.J Brown
results.story: The Juun J x Reebok Pump Omni Zone 2 ‘Wild Brown’ is drawn from a monochromatic three-piece pack made in collaboration with the Korean designer. The vintage ‘90s hoops shoe features a premium tan leather upper with perforated detailing at the toe box and quarter panel. Leather laces combine with Reebok’s Pump technology to deliver a secure fit. The signature TPU cage is rendered in a glossy finish, matching an added TPU heel piece marked with embossed Juun J branding. The mid-top rides on a lightweight EVA midsole, supported underfoot by a herringbone-traction rubber outsole.

results.name: Reebok Pump Omni Zone II Juun.J Black
results.story: Launching as part of a monochromatic three-piece pack with the Korean designer, the Juun J x Reebok Pump Omni Zone 2 ‘Black’ treats the ‘90s hoops shoe to a material upgrade. The premium black leather upper is accented with perforated paneling and secured with a combination of leather laces and Reebok’s retro Pump technology. Glossy black TPU is utilized on the wavy midfoot cage and an added heel piece embossed with Juun J branding. A matching black EVA midsole is enhanced with Hexalite cushioning

results.name: Reebok Club C 85 Pleasures (2021)
results.story: Conceived in partnership with the LA-based streetwear brand, the Pleasures x Reebok Club C 85 ‘Pine Green’ outfits the retro tennis shoe in a premium build. Black Cordura textile is utilized on the upper, accented with contrast white stitching and fortified with shaggy suede overlays in a lush green hue. Pleasures branding decorates a heart-shaped logo window on the lateral quarter panel and a woven tongue tag on the right shoe. A solid black rubber cupsole packs an EVA wedge for a cushioned ride.

results.name: Reebok Club C Legacy Pleasures
results.story: The Pleasures x Reebok Club C Legacy ‘Pure Grey’ delivers a modern take on the heritage tennis model, courtesy of the LA-based streetwear label founded by Alex James. A greyscale finish permeates a layered suede upper with breathable mesh construction at the vamp and collar. Pleasures branding adorns the lateral heel, woven tongue tag and sockliner. The low-top is anchored by a translucent rubber cupsole, featuring EVA cushioning and printed text on the lateral sidewall that reads ‘Pleasures Club C Legacy.’

Reebok Beatnik Beams x Needles
results.story: A triple collab shoe, the Reebok BEAMS x NEEDLES x Beatnik 'Black Purple' revives a beloved 90s outdoor sandal with a fresh twist. Japanese retailer and Keizo Shimizu’s label join forces for a December 2018 special edition that sees the retro Beatnik model dressed in allover suede with a Purple butterfly embroidered on top. A raw center seam and adjustable Velcro heel strap reinforce the design, while underfoot a jagged outsole keeps the sandal firmly rooted in heritage design.
